{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Alpha-amylase inhibitor inhibits mammalian alpha-amylases specifically, by forming a tight stoichiometric 1:1 complex with alpha-amylase. The inhibitor has no action on plant and microbial alpha amylases.</p>\r\n<p>A crystal structure has been determined for tendamistat, the 74-amino acid inhibitor produced by Streptomyces tendae that targets a wide range of mammalian alpha-amylases [[cite:PUB00027644]]. The binding of tendamistat to alpha-amylase leads to the steric blockage of the active site of the enzyme.  The crystal structure of tendamistat revealed an immunoglobulin-like fold that could potentially adopt multiple conformations. Such molecular flexibility could enable an induced-fit type of binding that would both optimise binding and allow broad target specificity.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "1ok0", "name" "Crystal Structure of Tendamistat"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR036379", "name" "Alpha-amylase inhibitor superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"pirsf" {"PIRSF001658" "Alpha-amylase inhibitor, Streptomyces type"}, "smart" {"SM00783" "Alpha amylase inhibitor"}, "pfam" {"PF01356" "Alpha amylase inhibitor"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Alpha-amylase inhibitor", "short" "A-amylase_inhib"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 7, "domain_architectures" 3, "proteomes" 80, "taxa" 253, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 212, "sets" 0, "proteins" 212, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 162}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR000833", :literature {"PUB00027644" {"URL" nil, "issue" "Pt 10", "authors" ["Konig V" "Vertesy L" "Schneider TR."], "ISO_journal" "Acta Crystallogr. D Biol. Crystallogr.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1107/S0907444903015828", "medline_journal" "Acta Crystallogr D Bio